==Spanish==

===Alternate Spellings===
* [[chupacabra]]

===Etymology===
[[chupar]], ''to [[suck]]'' + [[cabra]], ''[[goat]]''

===Noun===
{{es-noun-m|pl=chupacabras}}

# Literally “goat sucker”. A monster said to suck the blood from goats in [[Puerto Rico]] and [[Mexico]]. Known in many other Latin American countries including [[Peru]], [[Argentina]], [[Uruguay]]{{,}} and [[Chile]].

